definition.value: This is an AE which is tumours that form in the tissues of salivary glands.
This is an AE which is a concretion of material, usually mineral salts, that forms in an organ or duct of the salivary gland.
This is an AE which is a type of salivary gland diseases.
This is an AE which is tumours that form in the tissues of salivary glands.
This is an AE which is exocrine glands that produce saliva through a system of ducts and feels pain.
This is an AE which is the movement of material from one point to another, such as a secreted chemical substance from a salivary  gland.
This is an AE which is a break in the inner lining of the stomach, the first part of the small intestine, or sometimes the lower esophagus.
This is an AE which is an infection of a genus of anaerobic, Gram-positive, non-spore forming bacteria .

This is an AE which is a condition in which an untreated ulcer has burned through the mucosal wall in a segment of the gastrointestinal tract (e.g., the stomach or colon) allowing gastric contents to leak into the abdominal cavity.
This is an AE which is an abscess adjacent to the anus.
This is an AE which is redness of the perianal skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries.
This is an AE which is a chronic motility disorder characterized by effortless regurgitation of most meals following consumption, due to the involuntary contraction of the muscles around the abdomen.
This is an AE which is the expulsion of material from the pharynx, or esophagus, usually characterized by the presence of undigested food or blood.
This is an AE which can present with sonographic findings similar to hypertrophic pyloric stenosis.
This is an AE which is a narrowing of the opening from the stomach to the first part of the small intestine (the pylorus).
This is an AE which causes pulmonary atelectasis, secondary pneumonia, and respiratory failure is a frequent complication particularly in patients recovering from abdominal and thoracic surgery.
This is an AE which is mucus with purulent that is coughed up from the lower airways (the trachea and bronchi).
This is an AE which is complicated inflammation of the appendix.
This is an AE which is having more body fat than is optimally healthy.
This is an AE which is a symptom of pregnancy that involves nausea or vomiting.
This is an AE which is the inflammation of the epiglottis—the flap at the base of the tongue that prevents food entering the trachea (windpipe).
This is an AE which is defined as a condition in which a person does not have the physical or financial capability to eat sufficient food to meet basic nutritional needs for a sustained period.
This is an AE which is a severe deficiency in caloric energy intake, below the level needed to maintain an organism's life.
This is an AE which is a type of inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) that may affect any segment of the gastrointestinal tract from the mouth to the anus.
This is an AE which is a slight bulge in the small intestine present at birth and a vestigial remnant of the omphalomesenteric duct (also called the vitelline duct or yolk stalk).
This is an AE which is a person whose body weight is considered too low to be healthy.
This is an AE which is a condition of excessive air swallowing, which goes to the stomach.
This is an AE which is vascular structures in the anal canal.
This is an AE which is a type of gastroenteritis that results in bloody diarrhea.
This is an AE which is when a loop of intestine twists around itself and the mesentery that supports it, resulting in a bowel obstruction.
